.SH NAME
dotty-profile - Manage system profiles that travel across machines.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty profile  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Profiles are per-machine configuration sets — a Brewfile today; prompt and
terminal themes later — stored under $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/dotty/ so a public
dotfiles repository can carry them. One profile is active at a time, named by
the active-profile symlink.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for profile


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty profile new --name=work --description="work laptop"
  dotty profile activate
  dotty profile activate --name=personal
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty(1)\fP, \fBdotty-profile-activate(1)\fP, \fBdotty-profile-new(1)\fP
